    Why C(i+a[i], i+1)?

    Explanation from known editorial:

We only require that white cells have 0. The known solution in the second C++ code is:

            for (int i=0; i<=n; i++) {
                if (a[i]==0) break;
                ans = (ans + C(i+a[i], i+1)) % mod;
            } So they are summing C(i+a[i], i+1) for i from 0 to n until a[i]>0.
